grep uses Basic Regular Expressions (BRE). For full regex power, use:
grep -E for Extended Regex
grep -P for Perl-compatible Regex (only in some systems)
grep -i for case-insensitive
grep -v to invert match


grep -E "[0-9]{3}-[0-9]{3}-[0-9]{4}" file.txt
grep -E "[a-zA-Z0-9._]+@[a-zA-Z]+\.[a-z]{2,4}" file.txt
grep -i "linux" file.txt
grep -v "error" logs.txt
